    <div class="kt-accordion-item">
        <a class="kt-menu-link accordion-sub-item" tabindex="0" title="The flow of charge through electric circuits is discussed in detail. The variables which cause and hinder the rate of charge flow are explained and the mathematical application of electrical principles to series, parallel and combination circuits is presented." href="/tutorial/electric-circuits" aria-label="The flow of charge through electric circuits is discussed in detail. The variables which cause and hinder the rate of charge flow are explained and the mathematical application of electrical principles to series, parallel and combination circuits is presented." role="link">
            <span class="kt-menu-title">Electric Circuits</span>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
                <div class="kt-menu-item " data-navpath="/tutorial/magnetic-fields-and-electromagnetism" data-navhref="/tutorial/magnetic-fields-and-electromagnetism">
    <div class="kt-accordion-item">
        <a class="kt-menu-link accordion-sub-item" tabindex="0" title="Magnetic Fields and Electromagnetism explores the basic concepts which govern magnetic fields, magnetic forces, and the interrelation between electricity and magnetism. This chapter covers a variety of topics that highlight how electric currents create magnetic fields, providing insight into a wide range of phenomena and technologies." href="/tutorial/magnetic-fields-and-electromagnetism" aria-label="Magnetic Fields and Electromagnetism explores the basic concepts which govern magnetic fields, magnetic forces, and the interrelation between electricity and magnetism. This chapter covers a variety of topics that highlight how electric currents create magnetic fields, providing insight into a wide range of phenomena and technologies." role="link">
            <span class="kt-menu-title">Magnetic Fields and Electromagnetism</span>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
                <div class="kt-menu-item " data-navpath="/tutorial/electromagnetic-induction" data-navhref="/tutorial/electromagnetic-induction">
    <div class="kt-accordion-item">
        <a class="kt-menu-link accordion-sub-item" tabindex="0" title="Electromagnetic induction explores how changing magnetic fields can produce electric currents. This chapter introduces the key ideas behind Faraday&#x2019;s and Lenz&#x2019;s Laws and explains how they form the basis of generators, transformers, and many everyday technologies. Through clear examples and visual explanations, students discover how magnetism and electricity are intertwined." href="/tutorial/electromagnetic-induction" aria-label="Electromagnetic induction explores how changing magnetic fields can produce electric currents. This chapter introduces the key ideas behind Faraday&#x2019;s and Lenz&#x2019;s Laws and explains how they form the basis of generators, transformers, and many everyday technologies. Through clear examples and visual explanations, students discover how magnetism and electricity are intertwined." role="link">
            <span class="kt-menu-title">Electromagnetic Induction</span>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
                <div class="kt-menu-item " data-navpath="/tutorial/vibrations-and-waves" data-navhref="/tutorial/vibrations-and-waves">
    <div class="kt-accordion-item">
        <a class="kt-menu-link accordion-sub-item" tabindex="0" title="The nature, properties and behaviors of waves are discussed and illustrated; the unique nature of a standing wave is introduced and explained." href="/tutorial/vibrations-and-waves" aria-label="The nature, properties and behaviors of waves are discussed and illustrated; the unique nature of a standing wave is introduced and explained." role="link">
            <span class="kt-menu-title">Vibrations and Waves</span>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
                <div class="kt-menu-item " data-navpath="/tutorial/sound-waves" data-navhref="/tutorial/sound-waves">
    <div class="kt-accordion-item">
        <a class="kt-menu-link accordion-sub-item" tabindex="0" title="The nature of sound as a longitudinal, mechanical pressure wave is explained and the properties of sound are discussed. Wave principles of resonance and standing waves are applied in an effort to analyze the physics of musical instruments." href="/tutorial/sound-waves" aria-label="The nature of sound as a longitudinal, mechanical pressure wave is explained and the properties of sound are discussed. Wave principles of resonance and standing waves are applied in an effort to analyze the physics of musical instruments." role="link">
            <span class="kt-menu-title">Sound Waves</span>
        </a>
    </div>
</div>
                <div class="kt-menu-item " data-navpath="/tutorial/light-waves-and-colors" data-navhref="/tutorial/light-waves-and-colors">
    <div class="kt-accordion-item">
        <a class="kt-menu-link accordion-sub-item" tabindex="0" title="The behavior of light waves is introduced and discussed; polarization, color, diffraction and interference are introduced as supporting evidence of the wave nature of light. Color perception is discussed in detail." href="/tutorial/light-waves-and-colors" aria-label="The behavior of light waves is introduced and discussed; polarization, color, diffraction and interference are introduced as supporting evidence of the wave nature of light. Color perception is discussed in detail." role="link">
            <span class="kt-menu-title">Light Waves and Colors</span>
        </a>
    </div>
