        <a class="kt-menu-link accordion-sub-item" tabindex="0" title="Our Circular Motion and Gravitation unit represents an effort to apply Newton&#x27;s laws to the explanation of why objects move in circles. Newton&#x27;s law of universal gravitation is presented and explained in an effort to explain and analyze the motion of orbiting satellites, including the motion of planets and moons about their central bodies. The set of Video Tutorials below describe all sorts of applications of circular motion principles." href="/video-tutorial/circular-and-satellite-motion" aria-label="Our Circular Motion and Gravitation unit represents an effort to apply Newton&#x27;s laws to the explanation of why objects move in circles. Newton&#x27;s law of universal gravitation is presented and explained in an effort to explain and analyze the motion of orbiting satellites, including the motion of planets and moons about their central bodies. The set of Video Tutorials below describe all sorts of applications of circular motion principles." role="link">
