        Forces in 2D (5)
    </a>
</li>
                
<li data-navpath="/video-tutorial/momentum-collisions-and-explosions" data-navhref="/video-tutorial/momentum-collisions-and-explosions">
    <a class="visually-hidden-focusable" aria-keyshortcuts="ArrowUp ArrowDown Left Right" title="Our Momentum, Explosions, and Collisions unit represents an effort to apply momentum and momentum conservation principles in order to understand and analyze a variety of physical situations. The set of Video Tutorials below describe all sorts of applications of momentum principles to the analysis of explosions and collisions." href="/video-tutorial/momentum-collisions-and-explosions" aria-label="Our Momentum, Explosions, and Collisions unit represents an effort to apply momentum and momentum conservation principles in order to understand and analyze a variety of physical situations. The set of Video Tutorials below describe all sorts of applications of momentum principles to the analysis of explosions and collisions." role="link">
        Momentum, Collisions and Explosions (7)
    </a>
</li>
                
<li data-navpath="/video-tutorial/work-and-energy" data-navhref="/video-tutorial/work-and-energy">
    <a class="visually-hidden-focusable" aria-keyshortcuts="ArrowUp ArrowDown Left Right" title="Our Work, Energy, and Power unit represents an effort to present a model of energy as a tool for analyzing the motion of an object. The model relies on the confidence that energy can be kept track of; and because it can, we are able to make predictions of how fast an object will move, how hight it will go, and how far it will slide. The set of Video Tutorials below describe all sorts of applications of work and energy to the analysis of physical situations." href="/video-tutorial/work-and-energy" aria-label="Our Work, Energy, and Power unit represents an effort to present a model of energy as a tool for analyzing the motion of an object. The model relies on the confidence that energy can be kept track of; and because it can, we are able to make predictions of how fast an object will move, how hight it will go, and how far it will slide. The set of Video Tutorials below describe all sorts of applications of work and energy to the analysis of physical situations." role="link">
        Work and Energy (12)
    </a>
</li>
                
<li data-navpath="/video-tutorial/circular-and-satellite-motion" data-navhref="/video-tutorial/circular-and-satellite-motion">
    <a class="visually-hidden-focusable" aria-keyshortcuts="ArrowUp ArrowDown Left Right" title="Our Circular Motion and Gravitation unit represents an effort to apply Newton&#x27;s laws to the explanation of why objects move in circles. Newton&#x27;s law of universal gravitation is presented and explained in an effort to explain and analyze the motion of orbiting satellites, including the motion of planets and moons about their central bodies. The set of Video Tutorials below describe all sorts of applications of circular motion principles." href="/video-tutorial/circular-and-satellite-motion" aria-label="Our Circular Motion and Gravitation unit represents an effort to apply Newton&#x27;s laws to the explanation of why objects move in circles. Newton&#x27;s law of universal gravitation is presented and explained in an effort to explain and analyze the motion of orbiting satellites, including the motion of planets and moons about their central bodies. The set of Video Tutorials below describe all sorts of applications of circular motion principles." role="link">
        Circular and Satellite Motion (13)
    </a>
</li>
                
<li data-navpath="/video-tutorial/static-electricity" data-navhref="/video-tutorial/static-electricity">
    <a class="visually-hidden-focusable" aria-keyshortcuts="ArrowUp ArrowDown Left Right" title="Our Static Electricity unit focuses on the topic of how objects become electrically charge and the effect of such charges on other objects in the surrounding area.  The set of Video Tutorials below represent a systematic approach to understanding charge, charging methods, and the effect charges have on other objects." href="/video-tutorial/static-electricity" aria-label="Our Static Electricity unit focuses on the topic of how objects become electrically charge and the effect of such charges on other objects in the surrounding area.  The set of Video Tutorials below represent a systematic approach to understanding charge, charging methods, and the effect charges have on other objects." role="link">
        Static Electricity (15)
    </a>
</li>
                
<li data-navpath="/video-tutorial/electric-circuits" data-navhref="/video-tutorial/electric-circuits">
    <a class="visually-hidden-focusable" aria-keyshortcuts="ArrowUp ArrowDown Left Right" title="Our Electric Circuits unit focuses on the nature of moving charge in electric circuits. Key quantities like electric potential, electric power, current, and resistance are presented in a development manner and the mathematical connections between them is phased in.  The set of Video Tutorials below establishes the foundation for understanding electric circuits." href="/video-tutorial/electric-circuits" aria-label="Our Electric Circuits unit focuses on the nature of moving charge in electric circuits. Key quantities like electric potential, electric power, current, and resistance are presented in a development manner and the mathematical connections between them is phased in.  The set of Video Tutorials below establishes the foundation for understanding electric circuits." role="link">
        Electric Circuits (16)
    </a>
</li>
                
<li data-navpath="/video-tutorial/vibrations-and-waves" data-navhref="/video-tutorial/vibrations-and-waves">
    <a class="visually-hidden-focusable" aria-keyshortcuts="ArrowUp ArrowDown Left Right" title="Our Vibrations and Waves unit addresses the topic of vibrating objects and the relationship between vibrational motion and wave motion.  The set of Video Tutorials below lays a solid foundation for understanding the nature of a wave, the properties of waves, the behaviors of waves, and the mathematics of waves." href="/video-tutorial/vibrations-and-waves" aria-label="Our Vibrations and Waves unit addresses the topic of vibrating objects and the relationship between vibrational motion and wave motion.  The set of Video Tutorials below lays a solid foundation for understanding the nature of a wave, the properties of waves, the behaviors of waves, and the mathematics of waves." role="link">
        Vibrations and Waves (16)
    </a>
</li>
                
<li data-navpath="/video-tutorial/sound-waves" data-navhref="/video-tutorial/sound-waves">
    <a class="visually-hidden-focusable" aria-keyshortcuts="ArrowUp ArrowDown Left Right" title="Our Sound Waves unit addresses the topic of the physics of sound.  The set of Video Tutorials below lays a solid foundation for understanding their generation by a vibrating object, their properties and behaviors, and their connection to the operation of musical instruments." href="/video-tutorial/sound-waves" aria-label="Our Sound Waves unit addresses the topic of the physics of sound.  The set of Video Tutorials below lays a solid foundation for understanding their generation by a vibrating object, their properties and behaviors, and their connection to the operation of musical instruments." role="link">
        Sound Waves (14)
    </a>
